  "name": "AWS Potential Federated Console Access via SigninToken Abuse",
  "description": "Detects a sequence where an attacker generates temporary federated credentials, uses them to request a SigninToken, and then performs a console login \u2014 all without MFA. This behavior simulates a browser session to gain interactive access to the AWS Console, bypassing standard login flows.",
